message.content:
cs.WEB, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.WEB is the most likely category as the paper discusses the development of single-page web applications using AJAX and explores the navigational model and user interface structure of the source application.
- cs.GR is also likely as the paper discusses Two Dimensional (2D) drawings on images and videos, which involves graphics and visualization.
- cs.CV is likely as the paper discusses real-time data binding between drawing modules on images and videos, which involves computer vision techniques.
- cs.HC is likely as the paper discusses user interface design and the navigational model of the source application, which involves human-computer interaction.
- cs.MM is also likely as the paper discusses the use of canvas drawing for images and videos, which involves multimedia processing.
